# ProcessMap Stage Runtime Navigation

Use this file as the compact navigation pack for Executor and Reviewer agents.
Copy to `.local/processmap/stage-runtime-navigation.md` if local details differ.

## Direct Stage Session URL

Stage URL: `https://stage.processmap.ru`

Direct stage session URL:

```text
https://stage.processmap.ru/app?workspace=ws_8b89c83ea810_main&project=e41791f9f7&session=1a5bd431d8
```

Equivalent env value:

```text
PROCESSMAP_STAGE_SESSION_URL="https://stage.processmap.ru/app?workspace=ws_8b89c83ea810_main&project=e41791f9f7&session=1a5bd431d8"
```

## Organization

`Роботизация производств`

If stage prompts for organization/workspace selection, enter this organization first.
Do not search default workspace unless the contour explicitly asks for it.

## Tabs

- `Diagram (BPMN)` — BPMN diagram/canvas.
- `Анализ процессов` — process analysis and Product Actions surfaces.
- `XML` — raw XML view.
- `DOC` — generated/process documentation surface.
- `DOD` — Definition of Done / checklist surface.

## Product Actions Path

1. Open `PROCESSMAP_STAGE_SESSION_URL` directly.
2. Select organization `Роботизация производств` if prompted.
3. Open tab `Анализ процессов`.
4. Use `Шаг и продукт` / `Действия с продуктом`.
5. Common buttons:
   - `Предложить действия через AI`
   - `Реестр действий`
   - `Добавить действие`
6. For registry checks, use the workspace/project/session registry entrypoints supplied by the contour; do not infer registry truth from BPMN XML.

## BPMN Sidebar/Canvas Notes

- `Diagram (BPMN)` is the BPMN canvas entrypoint.
- Canvas interactions can be sensitive to selection/focus and zoom/pan state.
- Sidebar contains BPMN properties and overlays relevant to selected elements.
- Use direct session URL and saved storage state before testing canvas behavior.
- Avoid mutating BPMN XML for read-only runtime proof.

## Current Focus Areas

- Product Actions AI suggestions and review/apply boundary.
- Product Actions registry navigation and session/project drilldown.
- Lane display L1 / L1 → L2 in analysis step tables.
- BPMN overlays and selection/focus visibility.
- Diagram performance around session open, tab switches, overlays, and analysis rendering.

## Agent Instruction

Executor and Reviewer agents must not search the path through Explorer unless the contour is explicitly about Explorer. Start from the direct session URL and saved storage state.

## Commands

```bash
node tools/stage-auth-save-storage-state.mjs
node tools/stage-open-session-proof.mjs analysis
node tools/stage-open-session-proof.mjs diagram
node tools/stage-open-session-proof.mjs xml
node tools/stage-open-session-proof.mjs doc
node tools/stage-open-session-proof.mjs dod
```
